---
import '../../styles/global.css';
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<BaseLayout title="Get an OpenAI API Key — DayBrief Guide">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 md:px-6 py-16 md:py-24">

    <div class="mb-12">
      <a href={`${base}/guide/`} class="text-sm text-db-blue hover:underline mb-4 inline-block">&larr; Back to setup guide</a>
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold text-db-text tracking-tight mb-4">Get an OpenAI API Key</h1>
      <p class="text-db-text-secondary text-lg">Create an OpenAI account and generate an API key for DayBrief.</p>
    </div>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <div class="bg-db-card border border-db-border rounded-2xl p-6">
        <h2 class="text-sm font-bold text-db-text mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
          <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-db-blue" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"/></svg>
          Prerequisites
        </h2>
        <ul class="text-sm text-db-text-secondary space-y-1.5">
          <li>An OpenAI account</li>
          <li>A funded billing setup for API usage</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12 space-y-10">
      <div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
          <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-lg bg-db-blue text-white text-sm font-bold flex items-center justify-center">1</span>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-extrabold text-db-text">Open your API dashboard</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="pl-11 text-db-text-secondary leading-relaxed space-y-3">
          <p>Go to <a href="https://platform.openai.com/api-keys" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-db-blue hover:underline font-medium">platform.openai.com/api-keys</a> and sign in.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
          <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-lg bg-db-blue text-white text-sm font-bold flex items-center justify-center">2</span>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-extrabold text-db-text">Create a new secret key</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="pl-11 text-db-text-secondary leading-relaxed space-y-3">
          <p>Click <strong class="text-db-text">Create new secret key</strong>.</p>
          <p>Give it a clear name (for example: <strong class="text-db-text">daybrief-prod</strong>) and copy the key immediately.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
          <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-lg bg-db-blue text-white text-sm font-bold flex items-center justify-center">3</span>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-extrabold text-db-text">Add the key to GitHub Secrets</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="pl-11 text-db-text-secondary leading-relaxed space-y-3">
          <p>In your repository, open <strong class="text-db-text">Settings &rarr; Secrets and variables &rarr; Actions</strong>.</p>
          <p>Create a secret named <code class="bg-db-surface px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded border border-db-border text-sm text-db-text">OPENAI_API_KEY</code> and paste your key.</p>
          <p>Then set <code class="bg-db-surface px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded border border-db-border text-sm text-db-text">ai.provider: "openai"</code> in your config.yaml.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-extrabold text-db-text mb-4">Model choice</h2>
      <p class="text-db-text-secondary text-sm mb-4">DayBrief lets you configure any GPT model name in <code class="bg-db-surface px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded border border-db-border text-xs text-db-text">ai.model</code>. A good default for cost/performance is <code class="bg-db-surface px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded border border-db-border text-xs text-db-text">gpt-5.4-nano</code>.</p>
    </section>

    <div class="bg-db-surface border border-db-border rounded-xl p-5">
      <p class="text-sm text-db-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
        <strong class="text-db-text">Tip:</strong> Start with a smaller model to validate your pipeline, then scale up if you need deeper analysis quality.
      </p>
    </div>

  </div>
</BaseLayout>
